<UserId.>102456544133251625904</UserId.>< Name>
Jim Mignano</Name>
<date>1615054276336< /date><rating>5</rating>< Text>
Best pizza and service in Santa Monica! Whether you're in the mood for a classic or something new, SaMo's pizza selection will satisfy. They even offer a hot cheetos pizza. I'm a personal fan of the Mediterranean, which has meatballs, two cheeses, and a perfect combination of fresh veggies and seasonings. They also have fresh salads and sandwiches.

The staff at SaMo are all friendly and clearly love pizza making. You can taste the high quality of ingredients, the prices are competitive, and service is quick.

They're conveniently located right across from SaMo College and just a half-hour walk/5-10 minute drive from the beach.</Text>

< review>
I really can't trust reviews.  I ordered this pizza based on the 4.6 star review. I should have ordered Domino's.  It would have been cheaper ($30 bucks for a large peppers/mush) and would have been as good.  This is the first pizza I ever had that was so tasteless we looked at each other and said "this tastes like nothing".  The ordering online and delivery was accurate and on time so the stars are for the service and not for the pizza.  I do wish that pizza deliveries would figure out how to get your pizza here hot.  I was not that far away and it got here at room temperature.  I would pay more for a delivery that is hot.  Go to Dominos and save money.<//review>

< Rating>
4< /Rating>
< Review>
The crust is nice and thin, very delicate! The sauce is very good and they fire it in a hot pizza oven. We ordered several personal size 10" pies, the pepperoni was great, but the cheese pies were a little inconsistent with the meltiness. They had a great special on a 10" cheese or pepperoni for 4.99 and 5.99 respectively, so we ordered a bunch of those. I also had a house salad that was pretty standard, but good. The pizza menu is pretty extensive, but also pretty expensive! Some of the personal size pies were like $20. I'd like to try the vegetarian pie, but don't wanna shell out $17 for a thin 10" pie from a strip mall pizza stand with 4 tables. Either step up the ambiance or drop the prices.</Review>

4<//rate>
<text>Back again at the place my grandson says have the best pizzas in the WORLD. Ah, to be young again ...

The pizzas ARE quite good and their method of ordering is quite easy. You can order a pizza straight off of their menu or customize it pretty much any way you can imagine. Think of it like Subway - except the pizzas are terrific and delivered to your table piping hot.

There is a great vibe to this place and it is catchy. My grandson loves the condiment area (but likes the garlic way too much). they have a huge tree in the building along with some very neat pizza ovens. Make sure you try the Nutella Calzone.

Definitely will be back again when visiting the grandchildren. We could use something like this in New Jersey!< /text>< Pictures>

< user_name>
Walter Nissen</user_name>
<Time>1533219293833</Time>< rating>
4< /rating>
<review>Perfect for a casual after-work gathering, you can arrive, get some very good food quickly, sample some beers, and head out without having to worry about separate checks due to the innovative RFID wristband system. If you're coming for a full meal, though, you'll have to pace the courses yourself unless you want everything at once. And the beer, all rotating self-serve craft selections, is $8 a pint for Dechutes Black Butte Porter, so ironically it's probably not the place for a session, but rather an eclectic sampling. They even had a St. Bernardus on tap, which is very unusual. You also are responsible for getting your own water (in plastic cups). Staff were quite friendly, though I don't quite understand the counter service vibe in a place that is aiming for higher quality food. There are some misses, like the otherwise excellent open-faced burrata and prosciutto sandwich that was drenched with honey instead of olive oil. I hope they will work out some of the kinks because there is a lot to like at this new and distinctive addition to Livermore's growing food scene. Incidentally, all their promotional materials say "Established 2017", which is weird since their certificate of occupancy is dated June 2018.</review><Pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOHyR-jjdRnowzSc8ieDe4NfX9EtS_b7bvhIhk=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipM4fxdfJNykxfmBmirqy39FDYBy24LynBUcSos=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNs-fPIDnowVo99JS4ji7cQVkHI5U0FJgfF9MY=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]<//Pictures><Resp>None<//Resp><GmapID>0x808fe79f9a455555:0xdbe6d6cbc5400fb5</GmapID></record></dataset><record>

<rate>5<//rate>< Text>
I really like Hops and Sessions, its clean, no line, and the only wait is for the food. The food is fantastic by the way. The pretzels are loaded and the beer cheese is great, the hummus plate is the best I've had, and the burgers have that nice charred and fresh taste, like if fast food was made like the pictures are. 28 beer taps that rotate all the time. Hard to find something you won't like. The staff is also awesome and friendly, they dont judge how fast you return to pour another brew either.</Text>

<text>Before getting beer in front of the many dispensaries for a pint or glass of your own medicine, present your ID for age and credit card for checking out later.
An electronic wrist will then be provided that will serve as a key to activate the pour mechanism and as a reference for the drinks to be paid when leaving.
Many good selections and the place is neat and spacious, not really rowdy as it's sorta family-friendly. Some bites are available.<//text>< Response>

<rating>5< /rating>< Text>
A beer hall style venue with friendly and helpful staff on hand to explain the 3 ciders, 2 wines, and 25 beers on tap each representing Californian breweries with styles that quench all types of appetite. The brain meltdown begins when they tell you "the taps are self-service, just help yourself"...
90-minutes later I'm in heaven... Oh no wait, I blacked out, I'm actually at home lying down, mindblown, planning my return visit...

Hops and Sessions is wonderful but also a real test of your self control.

Amen.<//Text>

<Text>I first came here during their soft opening and was immediately impressed by their setup. I've seen other places in the U.S. and Europe where you can pour your own beer, but this is by far the nicest establishment I've seen so far. I enjoy the open space, shared communal tables and the ease of getting checked in. The staff as very helpful, and I always enjoy chatting with Thomas and Diego. They do serve food, which has been excellent. I've had almost everything on their menu, and still haven't had a bad meal yet. Hops & Sessions is a worthwhile visit the next time you find yourself in downtown Livermore.</Text><UserId.>113864002829577586370<//UserId.>< Rating>

<rate>3</rate>< text>
A novel gastropub concept that needs a little tweaking in the layout...  I understand that self service with such a wide selection is cool for a tap room.  However, I prefer a bartender or server.  The autotaps have slight learning curve but the big miss is their location.  They were placed on the wall nearest the entrance which limits the front counter.  Add to the fact that you have to order your food there and you have a crowd at the front of the pub and empty zones in the main area .  They need to just adjust the layout and it will go from good to great.< /text>

0x80dc019653e6401f:0x2ee6e3e1bd3d6c65< /gmap_id>
<user_id>110393585502605242351< /user_id>< text>
Went here for the first time on Saturday afternoon to have a little dare night for an early dinner. Very nice place and relaxed atmosphere. You can tell as you enter and see the menu that its a trendy venue. 10 dollars for a pretzel with queso and mustard. Id pay 7, max. Its a tasty pretzel, but a hard sell a second time at 10. Im knit picking on this one thing because its a simple dish made "fancy" with the addition of paper thin apple slices. A nice touch, but not necessary.
Skip the pretzel, head straight for a burger. The burgers are cooked perfectly! Super tasty and the veggies are fresh tasting and have beautiful color. I ended up having the basic burger and I WISHED it was just that. BHT puts a sauce with onions on it, or I was told it might have onions in it. I asked for no onions and no fault of the waitress she did not hear me. I should have restated that I can not eat onions because of a food sensitivity. I received the burger with onions and picked them off deciding to try to eat the burger instead of sending it back. I got one bite in before having to sending it back to be remade. The staff was very accommodating and gladly remade it for me. Bonus points there, but I was a little upset that anyone would come around and "encourage" me to speak up about the allergy. Its not an allergy, but because people don't think a sensitivity is necessary for precaution we typically just call it an allergy so people pay attention when we say "no onions".
Other than that one minor hiccup I would recommend this Tavern. And let me make it clear, the waitress who did not hear me initially say no onions was very polite and meant no harm. She was super friendly and showed concern. For that reason alone I will come back.

We have one item on the wish list for this place. A dog friendly patio. We will definitely be coming here on the weekday to check out their dinner scene on the weekday and have a drink.< /text>

This last visit however, was completely unacceptable. The chicken was freaking rotten, literally smelled rotten and the chicken wasn't even pink anymore it was discolored grey in spots and smelled funny. Lord forgive me for not checking the raw meat before I cooked it. I picked up a funny but faint scent when I first opened the chicken to bbq but just threw it all on the grill and chalked it up to my imagination, it was dark so nobody really noticed until we started eating. A few pieces had bits of funny taste here and there, I'm not saying the whole batch was bad, but there was definitely noticeably rotten chicken in there. I happened to have 3 pieces left of the 6 pounds we bought, and upon close inspection the chicken was freaking grey in spots and had a strong smell. Needless to say this was the last chance I give to la famosa, they've sold me borderline food before but it's never been ROTTEN, it's had minor off smells before but it's never been completely rotten like today. < username>
Ryan Mangiapane<//username>
< time>
1627100472377<//time>
<Rate>5< /Rate><review>I feel a responsibility to the people of southern San Diego to provide reviews that critically critique food, service, experience, and atmosphere, so the citizens of America's finest city can spend their hard-earned money on a restaurant worthy of patronage.

It is with great pleasure and pride in my community that I award Farmers Table with 5 golden stars. When we arrived with a reservation my wife and I were seated immediately! We reviewed the menu and were advised by the servers on some great options for beer and popular cocktails. My wife was stuck between 2 beers to order. The servers brought us samples so she could make a more educated choice and selected an airy Belgian beer. I ordered a blueberry moonshine cocktail. Both of these drinks were stupendous and set the tone for a night of luxury and impeccable flavors.

The sampling of drinks was the only start of the amazing service. For our meal, we ordered some specials - a surf and turf for my wife and game of the day for myself. My steak was seared with divine intervention. It melted in my mouth and the fat was perfectly rendered. My wife's steak, to her dismay, was slightly overcooked. We informed the server and the chefs promptly seared a new stake to her liking. The gravy was an exquisite blend of chocolate and red wine glazed over the meat like a chocolate dream.

For my wife's stake being slightly overcooked, our Server provided a desert free of charge. A bread pudding topped with a scoop of vanilla ice cream and a few fresh strawberries and blueberries drizzled on the plate. The desert was incredible - I am not typically a fan of bread pudding and I ate most of it.

I feel so much guilt for not having the vocabulary to describe how incredible our experience at Farmer's Table was. Kudos to the staff, the chef, and the managers of this new location. You have earned two loyal customers and I am proud to say Chula Vista has a new affordable and high-quality restaurant in our neighborhood.

Thank you so much for the great evening.< /review>< Pictures>

I just want to add that if have high expectations you might be disappointed. I Really wanted to like this place! The service was great and very cute decor. <Review>(Translated by Google) Very attentive service, and all four of us enjoyed our breakfast.

Over half the menu is American comfort food, but there are many other dishes with things like goat cheese or truffle oil, which they also prepare well.

Surprise: the chilaquiles were great - crisp and with very zesty green (tomatillo) sauce.

Good attention to ventilation as well.

Very attentive service, and our breakfast dishes were rich.

More than half of the breakfast menu looks like typical US food - "comfort food" - but also variety with unusual ingredients.

A surprise: the green chilaquiles were delicious: crispy chips and a very tasty sauce.

And attention to public health, too.

(Original)
Very attentive service, and all four of us enjoyed our breakfast.

Over half the menu is American comfort food, but there are many other dishes with things like goat cheese or truffle oil, which they also prepare well.

Surprise: the chilaquiles were great - crisp and with very zesty green (tomatillo) sauce.

Good attention to ventilation as well.

<Text>I called in advance of making my selection to come to Big O for my purchase.  I was told to come after 3pm.  I arrived at 3pm on Thursday, Feb. 14.  It took three hours to change my tires.  I had to miss a 6pm meeting.  I didn't expect to spend three hours at Big O Tires.

Sean ensured me that I would not be out of pocket from replacement and that I would receive new lock and key by Monday, Feb. 18.  It is Tuesday, Feb. 19; I haven't heard from Sean; and my tires are exposed for theft. Needless to say, I am not happy.

I wasn't offered to keep one of my tires for use as a spare. All of my tires were disposed of.

Unfortunately, I will now have to take time away from work to come resolve and I have to take time to call Sean.  There was no additional compensation offered for my inconvenience.

< Review>
Complete 5 star experience. Platinum Jewelry & Loan is by far the best pawn shop in the Antelope Valley. No one beats their rates and also, their selection of jewelry, coins as well as guitars. Gary and the entire service staff are very friendly, knowledgeable and more than fair for when it comes time to make a deal (especially when compared to the competition).
And to top it all off- they even polished my diamond ring when I paid the ticket. Gary did a fantastic job on the ring and its never shined better. No one else in LA offers services like that. I highly recommend Platinum Jewelry and Loan especially, if you are in a tight bind like how I was. They will help and the store is an asset to the local community.

Thanks again Gary and Victor.</Review>

<Rating>5<//Rating>< review>
Shops in Palmdale are total rip off people giving about 10 - 20% of melt price on gold. Weigh your gold. Know the current price and these guys will work with you. Of course they low ball you that is the name of the game but they did meet my offer. I talk to Fernado or Damien. They are polite and kind people but yeah this is not a super friendly type of business. I have been twice and would go again if I needed to. Roomy and clean....I felt totally safe and even the parking lot is monitored so safe going in too...in daylight of course. Easy to find building....nothing else is that color anywhere near so just keep your eyes open.

Very few items for shopping...lots of jewelry though. No random crap everywhere or large musical instruments or stuff like that....I think there were some electronics but I was not there to shop.

The scale is not where you can see it so for you own peace of mind weigh it at home. Coins make good counter weights to get pretty close. Coin weights are standard and on line.</review>
